commitResults.messageBody: Update use cases section for add, delete and view list in Developer Guide

Use cases are enumerated for easier inclusions in other use cases.

Inclusions are utilised in the use cases for pairing and tagging
contacts to minimise low-level steps. The use case for listing all
contacts is also used in many other use cases, includign pairing and
tagging.

Specific details are added to error messages in the use cases for pairing
and tagging to better understand what the error is.
Add Pair command functionality

The delete command does not consider the pairedWith attribute.

Let's ensure that the delete command throws an exception when a paired
contact is to be deleted.

The command only uses delete as the command keyword to execute the
command.

Let's add more alternate keywords del, rm, remove which can also be used
in place of delete.

commitResults.messageTitle: Merge branch 'branch-deleteContacts' of https://github.com/sdevih/tp into branch-deleteContacts
Add test cases for delete command
commitResults.messageBody:
The delete case do not test the addtional keywords added.

Let's ensure that the del, rm and remove keywords work as per normal
when executing the delete command.

The use of * in import statements was removed for clarity and better
understanding.

The addressbook does not unpair a volunteer and befriendee.

Let's add a UnpairCommand class to allow unpairing between volunteer and
befriendee, which would allow deleting of contacts.

Let's add test cases to check if the UnpairCommand class works as intended.

The unpair test case and command is updated to reflect the change from
uid to name for the pairedWith attribute.
